學習規範 Course Policy
	    1 This course values greatly on students' on-time and full participation with their group members. The number of group members is 4. Group members will receive an evaluation from each other which will be the base of the individual score of each member.[1]
2 Students are not allowed to use a cellphone or have access to internet during the class time.[2]
3 Notes regarding the evaluation of late-submitted homework, anonymous students' instant feedbacks, recommendation letter, please refer to the Moodle website.[3]
4 All written assignments must be uploaded to the MOODLE website (http://moodle.ncku.edu.tw/). To facilitate group oral presentation, a Power Point document of the presentation content is required. For details in preparing the PPT document, please download ‘Guidelines for PPT Present-Undergraduate Students’ from the Moodle website.[4]
5 On your presentation day, prepare hardcopies for every classmate. The layout of your PPT hardcopy for student: 列印/講義/純粹黑白/6張投影片 (i.e. 6 slides in each page)[5]. More than 6 slides in one pages is not reader-friendly at all.
6 To improve the teaching efficiency, May audio-tapes most lectures for self examination. With students' consent, one to two faculty members will sit in the class to observe May's teaching. At the end of the semester, students will be consulted whether they agree to have their verbal or written participation included as the research data.[6] 
[1]本課程重視小組學習，成員會互相評比組員參與情形，此評量成績將列入每位組員個人小組成績計算之考量。
[2]上課嚴禁學生使用手機或上網。
[3]關於作業遲交之計分方式、不記名教學意見即時回饋、推薦信，請參考Moodle。
[4]編輯PPT檔案時，務必依循Guidelines for PPT present-Undergraduate Students之規定。
[5]報告當日請準備給所有同學之報告講義，每頁6張投影片，超過每張超過6頁增加閱讀困難。
[6]本課程屬於任課老師May個人的教學改善計畫之一，May上課過程會錄音便於自我檢視教學成效。在同學同意下，會安排一至二位教師列座觀察May之教學。May並會於期末時，徵詢同學意願是否同意將學生的個人參與，列為教學研究資料。同學可以於期末依照個人意願選擇列入或不列入研究資料。      

